<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Advanced Detectors on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/unsupported-field-workshops/1-imt/detectors/advanced-detectors/</link><description>Recent content in Advanced Detectors on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/unsupported-field-workshops/1-imt/detectors/advanced-detectors/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Historical Anomaly Detector</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/unsupported-field-workshops/1-imt/detectors/advanced-detectors/wizard-baseline/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/unsupported-field-workshops/1-imt/detectors/advanced-detectors/wizard-baseline/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="objective"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Objective&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#objective" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Create a historical baseline anomaly detector using the detector wizard and examine the generated alert message.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id="step-1--create-the-detector"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Step 1 – Create the Detector&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#step-1--create-the-detector" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Navigate to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Alerts &amp;amp; Detectors → &lt;button class="btn-inline btn-inline--filled" type="button" style="--btn-color: #1d5d99"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Create Detector&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/button&gt; → Custom Detector&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ADD YOUR INITIALS&lt;/strong&gt; before the proposed detector name.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="callout callout--info"&gt;&lt;span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/&gt;&lt;line x1="12" y1="16" x2="12" y2="12"/&gt;&lt;line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12.01" y2="8"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class="callout__body"&gt;&lt;p class="callout__title"&gt;Naming the detector&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;It&amp;rsquo;s important that you add your initials in front of the proposed detector name.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Edit in SignalFlow</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/unsupported-field-workshops/1-imt/detectors/advanced-detectors/edit-in-signalflow/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/unsupported-field-workshops/1-imt/detectors/advanced-detectors/edit-in-signalflow/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="objective"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Objective&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#objective" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Refactor the wizard-generated detector to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Separate threshold calculation from alert logic&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Compose multiple conditions in a single &lt;code&gt;detect()&lt;/code&gt; statement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Introduce a static operational guardrail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Surface dynamic anomaly thresholds for reuse in alert messages&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id="edit-in-signalflow"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Edit in SignalFlow&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#edit-in-signalflow" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;From the detector action menu in the upper right hand corner &lt;strong&gt;(⋯)&lt;/strong&gt;, select &lt;strong&gt;Edit in SignalFlow&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should still be in the Detector UI for the detector you just saved, if not:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Update Alert Message and Alert Rule</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/unsupported-field-workshops/1-imt/detectors/advanced-detectors/update-message/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/unsupported-field-workshops/1-imt/detectors/advanced-detectors/update-message/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="objective"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Objective&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#objective" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Customize the alert message to accurately reflect the multi-condition detection logic by:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Explaining why the wizard-generated message is removed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Referencing published threshold streams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Explicitly communicating both the historical anomaly and static guardrail conditions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id="step-1--save-the-detector"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Step 1 – Save the Detector&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#step-1--save-the-detector" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Click &lt;button class="btn-inline btn-inline--filled" type="button" style="--btn-color: #1d5d99"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Save&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/button&gt; in the upper right corner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id="step-2--edit-alert-message"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Step 2 – Edit Alert Message&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#step-2--edit-alert-message" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Navigate to the detector’s &lt;strong&gt;Alert Rules&lt;/strong&gt; tab.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>